<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-01-0686 </DOCNO><TEXT>Radioactivity is certainly not limited to hermetically sealed nuclearreactors or research laboratories. Radioactivity and radiation are apart of our daily life. The article is intended to explain basic termsof radioactivity, the sources of radioactive radiation and the dose ratesemitted by them. The radiation from cosmic radiation and terrestrialradiation, the radiation doses in the vicinity of power stations andthe genetically significant annual dose are specially described.</TEXT></DOC>